// include/ezmk/i18n_keys.def
//
// Single source of truth for all i18n string keys (0.2.6+).
//
// Each key is declared exactly once here with EZMK_I18N_KEY(name). Both the
// `I18nKey` enum (i18n.hpp) and the enum→JSON-key-name mapping (i18n.cpp
// key_name()) are generated from this list, so they can never drift out of
// sync. Adding a new user-visible string is now a three-step, hard-to-forget
// process:
//   1. add EZMK_I18N_KEY(new_key) here,
//   2. add "new_key" to locale/en.json and locale/zh.json,
//   3. rebuild (build.sh re-embeds the locale data).
//
// The `name` MUST match the JSON key string verbatim.

